scanf in c and cin in c++ will get input from stdin,and store input ,but if there is a space in input ,they will only store the 
data before space!

how to get complete data,even if data contain space?
in c ,you can use "char * get(char *line)";
in c++, you can use getline(cin,line)("istream& getline(istream& is,string& str)")!
